# Blog CMS — environment configuration
#
# Copy to `.env` and adjust. Everything here has a sensible default except the
# AI provider, which the blog-editor agent needs in order to run.

# --- Database (optional) ---------------------------------------------------
# Unset = zero-config SQLite at ./.sovrium/database.db (the default).
# Set a Postgres URL to use Postgres instead.
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:pass@localhost:5432/blog

# --- AI provider (required to run the blog-editor agent) -------------------
# The /admin/ai-editor assistant needs an AI provider. Without these vars the
# pages still serve, but the server refuses to start while an `agents:` block
# is present, so set a provider below.
#
# Local, free, frugal-by-default — run Ollama (https://ollama.com) and pull a model:
AI_PROVIDER=ollama
AI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
AI_MODEL=llama3.1
#
# Or use a cloud provider instead (comment out the Ollama lines above):
# AI_PROVIDER=anthropic
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# AI_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
#
# AI_PROVIDER=openai
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# AI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# --- Email (optional) ------------------------------------------------------
# Unset = email features disabled (sign-in still works). Set to enable.
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.example.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USER=
# SMTP_PASSWORD=
